@NODE intro "Introduction"
		Introduction
		------------
	This is basically a collection of AREXX scripts and settings instructions that will get a Windows internet shortcut to work via AWeb or Ibrowse. There are 2 parts to it, the ability to export .url files for Windows users, and the ability to import them.
	I've been using this setup for quite some time, but when Chris Handley's OpenWinURL.lha appeared on Aminet (comm/www/OpenWinURL.lha), I figured there was a bit of demand for something like this, and decided to upload my version. I polished it up a bit first, though.
	The reason I came up with this system is my wife. She uses Windows XP, and likes to save .url shortcuts to the fileserver (I'm using a NASlite server on a P4 w/ 4 hard drives), and expected me to look at them on the Amiga. Got sick of copy & pasting urls out of multiview. So I set up AREXX scripts that not only parse the url out of such files and send them to my favorite browser, I created another script that exports .url files so either she or myself can view them if I find something she might like. (As much as I hate, loathe and despise Windows, the .url files are actually kind of handy!)

	@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE reqs "Requirements"

	You'll need the following to use RexxWinURL:
	
	Required:
	---------
	A Browser. (Kinda pointless without one) Tested on both:
		AWEB 3.4APL (http://aweb.sunsite.dk)
		Ibrowse 2.4 (http://www.ibrowse-dev.net)
	OpenURL (http://aminet.net/comm/www/OpenURL-7.6.lha)
	RXASL.library (http://aminet.net/util/rexx/rxasl.lha)
	ARexx installed
	
	Recommended:
	------------
	PowerIcons (http://aminet.net/util/wb/PowerIcons.lha)
	 The included icons are PowerIcons, as this is what I use. I'll probably upload another update with newicons, glowicons, mwb/classic icons, etc... when I have some time.
	DefIcons (http://aminet.net/util/wb/DefIcons44.lha)
	 DefIcons is useful for determining URL files, and setting the default tool.
	A Windows using friend/relative who always sends you (formerly) annoying .url files	
	@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE install "Installation instructions"

	Installation can be a bit hairy, as this thing uses several different programs, tied together via AREXX. There are 3 different AREXX scripts.
	ExportMSIEURL.ibrx	Exports a .url file from Ibrowse
	ExportMSIEURL.rexx	Exports a .url file from Aweb
	winURL.rexx		Imports a .url file wih OpenURL
	
	Put these scripts wherever you keep your Arexx stuff. The Ibrowse and Aweb scripts can go in the rexx directory in the browsers path, winURL.rexx can go in Rexx: or s: for example.

	I've decided to separate the installation into different programs.
	
	@{"Ibrowse" LINK "Ibrowse"}      @{"Aweb" LINK "Aweb"}      @{"Deficons" LINK "Deficons"}

	@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Ibrowse "Configuring Ibrowse"
		Ibrowse 2.4 Configuration
		-------------------------
	
	Copy the file winurl/Ibrowse/ExportMSIEURL.ibrx into either your ibrowse/rexx drawer, or wherever you keep your Ibrowse AREXX scripts.
	After starting Ibrowse, you need to open the preferences window (Under preferences->settings, or Ramiga-z). Everything you need to set-up will be available here.
	
		@{u}For importing .url files@{uu}
	Under General, MIME Types: Click the Add button for a new entry, with the following:
		MIME Type: text/url
		Extension: url
		Action: External viewer
		Viewer: c:rx
		Arguments s:winurl.rexx %r 
		(replace s: with the path you put winurl.rexx)
		@{"Screenshot" SYSTEM "multiview images/ibrowse/MIMEprefs.iff"}
	When you select a .url file via the open file menu, it will automatically go to the URL you want, assuming Ibrowse is configured in OpenURL.
		
		@{u}For exporting .url files@{uu}
	There are a couple of ways to do this, depending on how you would like to launch the script. The 2 I'll cover are the FAB menus (the pop-up when you right-click in the page) and the macro menu.

	@{b}Macro menu@{ub}
	Under GUI, Macros: Click the Add button for a new entry, with the following:
		Name: Export URL file
		Action: ARexx	rexx/ExportMSIEURL.ibrx
		(replace rexx/ with the path you put ExportMSIEURL.ibrx)
		@{"Screenshot" SYSTEM "multiview images/ibrowse/macroprefs.iff"}
	This will add a "Export URL file" menu to the Macros menu, which will open a file requester for the file location.

	@{b}FAB menu@{ub}
	Under GUI, FAB Menus:
	Drag "Submenu" from the left panel to the Page list in the right panel, enter Save as.. in the Name: field
	Drag "Custom" under the submenu option to the new sub-menu in the right, and edit the following:
		Name: .url file
		Action: ARexx	rexx/EportMSIEURL.ibrx	%u
		(replace rexx/ with the path you put ExportMSIEURL.ibrx)
		@{"Screenshot" SYSTEM "multiview images/ibrowse/fabprefs.iff"}
	This will ad a "Save as.." sub-menu in the fab menu, with .url file under it, which will start the script.
	
	@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE aweb "Aweb configuration"
	AWeb 3.4APL Configuration
	-------------------------
	
	Copy the file winurl/aweb/ExportMSIEURL.rexx to aweb/rexx/EportMSIEURL.rexx, or wherever you keep AWEB scripts.
	After starting AWeb, open the GUI and browser setting windows, under the settings menu.
	
		@{u}For importing .url files@{uu}
	In Browser settings, go to the Viewers tab. (#5) Click the Add button, and enter the following:
		Type: TEXT/URL
		Extensions: url Action: Extl. Program
		Name: c:rx
		Arguments: S:winURL.rexx %u
		(Replace S: with the path you put WinURL.rexx in)
		@{"Screenshot" SYSTEM "multiview images/aweb/MIMEprefs.iff"}
	This will redirect AWEB to the page specified in the .url file, assuming you have OpenURL set to Aweb.
	
		@{u}For exporting .url files@{uu}
	For this, you want to add a menu in the ARexx area. Or somewhere else, I guess, AWebb seems pretty configurable for this.
	In AWeb GUI Settings, go to the Menu tab. (#2) Scroll to the bottom of the list, and click Add. (Unless you want the menu item somewhere else, of course) Then enter the following:
		Type: Item Title: Export .url file @{i}A@{ui}: Whatever hotkey you want
		Command: SYSTEM c:rx AwebPath:rexx/ExportMSIEURL.rexx
		(Replace AwebPath:rexx/ with whatever path you put ExportMSIEURL.rexx in)
		@{"Screenshot" SYSTEM "multiview images/aweb/guiprefs.iff"}
	This will add a "Export .url file" menu under the ARexx menu.

	@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Deficons "Deficons Configuration"
		Deficons Configuration
		----------------------
	Look in the WinURL/Icons/ directory, find one you like, and copy it to Envarc:sys/def_URL.info and ENV:sys/def_URL.info
	Open the Deficons editor in sys:prefs. Click the Add button (above the Save button), and enter:
		Name: URL
	Use the down button until its somewhere in the "Ascii" sub-menu.
	Under Actions, hold down the Add ... button, and release the "PATTERN" option. Then enter:
		Pattern: #?.url
	Hold down the Add ... button again, and release the "MATCH" option. Enter the following:
		Offset: 0 Case sensitive: (Doesn't really matter, I keep it off)
		Match: [InternetShortcut]
		@{"Screenshot" SYSTEM "multiview images/deficons/deficonsprefs.iff"}
	Just to make sure the def_url.info icon is set properly, go to the settings, information menu, and make sure the icon is a project with a default tool of OpenURL.
	@{"Screenshot" SYSTEM "multiview images/deficons/iconprefs1.iff"}
	Now whenever you do a "show all", and see a .url file, double clicking it will open the browser and go to the specified website, in accordance with OpenURL's prefs.
	
	@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

