@NODE tips "Tricks n tips"
		Cool stuff this can do
		----------------------
		
	Especially with deficons installed, this can open web-pages from anything that can launch a project icon. This means you can do a "leave out" on a web-site, so you have quick access to Aminet, for example. Also, if you use Amidock, or ToolManager, you can maintain a hotlist with this. 
	One thing I like about it is the ability to store links on a fileserver, where everything on the LAN can access it. This is useful for pages everyone on the network frequents, and can be updated as needed by only modifying one file.
	Also, my webserver (an old X86 box running ServerElements NASLite, works great with both Windows and AmigaOS, via SMBFS) has an HTTP: port, which means everything from server status pages to .html files hosted on the server can be accessed directly via browser, making the .url files handy for locally hosted pages. 
	Also, the main reason for the program, for Windows people who not only send a .url file via floppy/email/whatever and expect you to use it, you can now do this without opening a text editor to copy & paste the url. Also, you can send .url files to these same people instead of copying and pasting links into an e-mail.
	You can annoy fellow Amiga users the same way windows users have, until you tell them about this file. :D
	
	@{"Back" link "Main"}
@ENDNODE
